### SmartBin UI/UX Cursor Rules

These rules align the mobile‑first hi‑fi Figma with the existing Next.js/Tailwind app. Follow them to keep styles, components, and flows consistent. Do not ship features that break these rules.

## Principles
- **Mobile‑first**: Target 390–430px width. Use `max-w-[430px] mx-auto` wrappers. Desktop just centers the mobile frame.
- **Single source of tokens**: All colors, radii, shadows, spacing live in CSS variables inside `app/globals.css` under `:root`/`@theme inline`.
- **Typography**: Use Inter for UI text. Apply with the utility class `font-inter`.
- **Atomic components**: Build reusable, testable components in `app/components/`.
- **Accessible**: Contrast ratio ≥ 4.5 for text; focus styles visible.

## Design Tokens (extendable)
Declare tokens in `app/globals.css` only. Reference tokens in Tailwind via CSS variables.

- **Colors**
  - `--color-primary-700`: Dark Green (for headers/cards)
  - `--color-primary-600`: Green (buttons/CTAs)
  - `--color-primary-500`: Light Green (accent)
  - `--color-accent-amber`: Amber (highlight words like “rupiah!”)
  - `--color-card`: Surface card bg
  - `--color-muted`: Muted text/icon
  - `--color-success`: Positive amounts
  - `--color-danger`: Negative amounts
  - `--gradient-primary`: Green gradient used on balance slider card

  Temporary hex suggestions (replace with Figma later):
  - `--color-primary-700: #0b5d3b`
  - `--color-primary-600: #0e7f4e`
  - `--color-primary-500: #14a160`
  - `--color-accent-amber: #ffbf3b`
  - `--color-card: #ffffff`
  - `--color-muted: #7a8b87`
  - `--color-success: #19c37d`
  - `--color-danger: #e24a4a`
  - `--gradient-primary: linear-gradient(90deg, #3aa55c 0%, #a8d672 100%)`

- **Radii**
  - `--radius-sm: 8px`  (list items)
  - `--radius-md: 12px` (cards)
  - `--radius-lg: 16px` (hero cards)
  - `--radius-pill: 999px` (chip/fab)

- **Shadows**
  - `--shadow-card: 0 6px 18px rgba(0,0,0,0.08)`
  - `--shadow-fab: 0 8px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.16)`

- **Typography**
  - Title/Large: `text-[22px] leading-7 font-semibold`
  - Body: `text-[14px] leading-5`
  - Label/Meta: `text-[12px] leading-4 text-[color:var(--color-muted)]`

  Font sizes (define as CSS variables in `@theme inline` and use via Tailwind utilities):
  - `--text-xs: 0.75rem` (12px); `--text-xs--line-height: calc(1 / 0.75)`
  - `--text-sm: 0.875rem` (14px); `--text-sm--line-height: calc(1.25 / 0.875)`
  - `--text-base: 1rem` (16px); `--text-base--line-height: calc(1.5 / 1)`
  - `--text-lg: 1.125rem` (18px); `--text-lg--line-height: calc(1.75 / 1.125)`
  - `--text-xl: 1.25rem` (20px); `--text-xl--line-height: calc(1.75 / 1.25)`
  - `--text-2xl: 1.5rem` (24px); `--text-2xl--line-height: calc(2 / 1.5)`
  - `--text-3xl: 1.875rem` (30px); `--text-3xl--line-height: calc(2.25 / 1.875)`
  - `--text-4xl: 2.25rem` (36px); `--text-4xl--line-height: calc(2.5 / 2.25)`
  - `--text-5xl: 3rem` (48px); `--text-5xl--line-height: 1`
  - `--text-6xl: 3.75rem` (60px); `--text-6xl--line-height: 1`
  - `--text-7xl: 4.5rem` (72px); `--text-7xl--line-height: 1`
  - `--text-8xl: 6rem` (96px); `--text-8xl--line-height: 1`
  - `--text-9xl: 8rem` (128px); `--text-9xl--line-height: 1`

## Layout Conventions
- **Page frame**: Wrap each page with `div.container` using `max-w-[430px] mx-auto min-h-screen bg-[var(--background)] text-[var(--foreground)] font-inter`.
- **Safe area**: Padding `pt-4 pb-24 px-4` to leave room for the bottom nav.
- **Bottom tab bar**: Fixed at bottom, elevated, notch FAB for Scan.

## Core Components (placeholders allowed)
- `BottomNav`: 3 tabs (Home, Scan, Saya). Center contains FAB (`Scan`), others are standard buttons. Keep labels under icons.
- `BalanceCard`: Shows balance, top up/withdraw buttons, progress slider, and points.
- `ActionGrid`: 4 circular actions (Duitin, Temuin, Anterin, Tukerin).
- `HeroCarousel`: Banner with image/illustration and pagination dots.
- `HistoryList`: Transaction list with icon, title, time, amount delta and points delta.
- `SectionHeader`: Title with optional right‑aligned small CTA.
- `Tag/Chip`: Small rounded labels.

Place components under `app/components/` using clear names and props. Keep logic separate from rendering when possible.

## Routing Map (proposed, matches existing)
- `/` → Home (dashboard + shortcuts)
- `/scan` → Camera/scan flow
- `/history` → Transaction history
- `/statistics` → Stats dashboard
- `/education` → Education grid
- `/payout` → Withdraw/Top‑up flows
- `/notifications` → List + settings
- `/rag` → Smarten AI Agent
- `/admin/*` → Admin screens

## State/Networking
- Reuse existing contexts and APIs. Do not change backend contracts.
- When updating points, follow the front‑end guard: only update with non‑decreasing numeric totals.
- Use placeholders for images/icons in `public/` until assets are delivered (`public/placeholders/*.svg|png`).

## Tailwind Usage
- Prefer utilities. For repeating patterns, create tiny components with class presets instead of new CSS.
- Gradients via inline style or `bg-[var(--gradient-primary)]` using `background-image: var(--gradient-primary)`.
- Rounded: `rounded-[var(--radius-md)]` etc.
- Shadow: `shadow-[var(--shadow-card)]` via `[box-shadow:var(--shadow-card)]` utility.

## Accessibility
- Touch targets ≥ 44px.
- Buttons must have `aria-label` when icon‑only.
- Color contrast >= WCAG AA.

## Testing
- Snapshot visual tests for components where feasible.
- Interaction tests around bottom nav, scan CTA, and list scrolling.

## Implementation Checklist (do in order)
1. Ensure tokens exist in `app/globals.css` (add/adjust variables only; keep theme block intact).
2. Create `BottomNav` with center FAB and wire to `/scan`.
3. Build `BalanceCard`, `ActionGrid`, `HeroCarousel`, `HistoryList` using placeholders.
4. Apply the mobile frame and safe‑area paddings across pages.
5. Replace legacy UI in `app/page.js` and related routes with new components, preserving existing data hooks.
6. Verify points update guard and error states.
7. QA pass at widths 360–430px.

## Notes
- Inter font is already wired via `.font-inter`. Use it globally on the container and override only when necessary.
- Keep code changes scoped; do not modify backend connection rules.


